Photo shared by Saint Hoax on September 04, 2021 tagging @fatblackluxury. May be an image of text that says 'Miss Rum Romping @FatBlackLuxury It's 2021 & Drake samples R. Kelly on one of the most anticipated albums of the year. Just tell us you don't care about Black girls + women, QUICKLY and GO! I'm so tired of BW & girls having to overlook & give up so much of ourselves to be apart of a culture we helped build.'.
Photo by Saint Hoax on September 04, 2021. May be an image of text.

Photo shared by Saint Hoax on September 04, 2021 tagging @m.4rs. May be an image of text that says 'King Mars @_M4RS Drake literally put R Kelly on his album and y'all just eating it up. Y'all really cap. It's "protect black women" until one of y'all favorite artist drop a project feat the abuser suddenly y'all make exceptions.'.

Photo by Saint Hoax on September 04, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'justyna @justynaroz_ drake sampling r.kelly and kanye featuring marilyn manson and da baby really shows you men don't care about women and their trauma huh'.

node.text: Climate change is wreaking havoc across the planet, meanwhile your politicians are too busy controlling women’s reproductive rights

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Saint Hoax on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Jodi @Hirshleft Good morning and welcome to America, where abortion is no longer legal and your home may float away in a climate change induced flood after you've caught a deadly virus assuming you haven't already been evicted.'.

Photo by Saint Hoax on September 02, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez @AOC We are running out of time to act on climate. Members of both parties engage in misleading rhetoric and funny math to convince the public we are addressing climate change more than we are & that includes parts of the current infrastructure plan. We need a Green New Deal now.'.

Photo by Saint Hoax on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Read Parable of the Sower by Octavia Butler @JoshuaPotash The pandemic is hitting the poor a lot harder than the rich. Climate change is hitting the poor a lot harder than the rich. Abortion bans hit the poor a whole lot harder than the rich. Rich folks and politicians know exactly what they're doing here, do you? guess wonder when the magnitude our reaction will match the magnitude of their actions.'.
